"Argyrou M., Demetropoulos A., Hadjichristophorou M.","Expansion of the macroalga Caulerpa racemosa and changes in softbottom macrofaunal assemblages in Moni Bay, Cyprus",1999,"Oceanologica Acta","22","5",,"517","528",,,10.1016/S0399-1784(00)87684-7,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0033197483&partnerID=40&md5=9d7ea0190d6ff41ba9b8ceb5997c21e4","Marine Biology and Ecology Section, Department of Fisheries, Natural Resources and Environment, 13 Aeolou Street, 1416 Nicosia, Cyprus","Argyrou, M., Marine Biology and Ecology Section, Department of Fisheries, Natural Resources and Environment, 13 Aeolou Street, 1416 Nicosia, Cyprus; Demetropoulos, A., Marine Biology and Ecology Section, Department of Fisheries, Natural Resources and Environment, 13 Aeolou Street, 1416 Nicosia, Cyprus; Hadjichristophorou, M., Marine Biology and Ecology Section, Department of Fisheries, Natural Resources and Environment, 13 Aeolou Street, 1416 Nicosia, Cyprus","The recent expansion of the Red Sea macroalga Caulerpa racemosa and its impact on the diversity and abundance of macrobenthos were examined and compared in the summers of 1992 and 1997, in Moni Bay, Cyprus. The phytobenthic community of the bay in 1992 was dominated by the seagrass Posidonia oceanica while, in 1997, the Lessepsian migrant C. racemosa became the most dominant, forming extensive mats. Changes in the vegetation system in Moni Bay have caused significant compositional changes in macrofaunal assemblages. A total of 178 individuals of 62 species are recorded. The composition of the macrofauna in 1992 was dominated by gastropods (44 %), crustaceans (22 %), bivalves (17 %), polychaetes (11%) and echinoderms (6 %). In 1997, the gastropods and crustaceans had decreased to 13 % and 16 % respectively, while, polychaetes had increased to 38 % becoming the most dominant taxon. Bivalves and echinoderms also increased to 22 % and 11%, respectively, in 1997. The proliferative growth of C. racemosa imposed successional changes on the macrofaunal assemblages in Moni Bay, Cyprus, between 1992 and 1997. It remains to be tested whether the expansion of C. racemosa is related to the increase of water temperature associated with global warming or nutrient inputs or with the differences in the life history characteristics of this migrant vs. native algal species.","Benthos; Caulerpa racemosa; Community composition; Lessepsian migrant; Moni Bay, Cyprus","colonization; community response; macroalga; soft-bottom environment; Cyprus; Caulerpa racemosa; Posidonia oceanica",,,,,,"Aleem, A.A., The occurrence of the sea-grass: Halophila stipulacea (forssk.) asch, on the west coast of egypt (1962) Bull. Fac. Sci., 4, pp. 79-84. , Univ. Alexandria; Argyrou, M., Hadjichristophorou, M., Demetropoulos, A., Ecological changes of softbottom macrobenthic assemblages in relation to the sewage outfall, in the Limassol Bay Cyprus, , eastern Mediterranean, Oebalia (accepted); Bilyard, G.R., The value of benthic infauna in marine pollution monitoring studies (1987) Mar. Poll. Bull., 18, pp. 581-585; D'Angelo, G., Gargiullo, S., (1987) Guida Alle Conchiglie Mediterranee, , Fabri Editori, Milano, 224 p; Demetropoulos, A., Marine molluscs of cyprus (part A) (1969) Fisheries Bulletin, Ministry Agriculture Nat. Res., Fisheries Dep., 2, pp. 1-15; Demetropoulos, A., Marine molluscs of cyprus (part B) (1971) Fisheries Bulletin, Ministry Agriculture Nat. Res., Fisheries Dep., 2, pp. 1-15; Demetropoulos, A., Hadjichristophorou, M., (1976) Echinodermata of Cyprus, Fisheries Bulletin, Ministry Agriculture Nat. Res., Fisheries Dep., pp. 1-74; Demetropoulos, A., Hadjichristophorou, M., Some additions to the knowledge of the malacofauna of cyprus (1976) Fisheries Bulletin, Ministry Agriculture Nat. Res., Fisheries Dep., 4, pp. 75-83; Fauvel, P., (1975) Polychetes Errantes, Faune De France, 5. , Kraus Reprint, Nendln/Liechtenstein, 488 p; Fischer, W., Schneider, M., Bauchot, M.L., (1987) MéDiterranée Et Mer Noire, Zones De